  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Consolidating and Expanding Institutions and Communities&apos; Capacity for Resilience to Natural Hazards in Tajikistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DIPECHO</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Female</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Under its programme for community-based Disaster Preparedness (DP) and Disaster Risk Reduction (DRR) in Tajikistan, Oxfam works at village level and with the Committee of Emergency Situations and Civil Defence (CoES) to increase resilience of local communities and institutions. The core strategy has been to support practices that enable rural communities and relevant institutions to work together to prepare for and respond to natural disasters. To that end, as DP/DRR, decentralisation and community participation are still underdeveloped concepts in the Tajik context, Oxfam has started building the capacity of the CoES&apos; East Khatlon branch in community-oriented DP/DRR. To complete this set of practices, communities in East Khatlon have been capacitated to better prepare for disasters.This new phase will focus on engaging more communities and mentoring the regional CoES in order to institutionalise this nascent, community-based DP/DRR capacity. By doing so, the Action aims to address the observed disruptions in the cycle of community-oriented DP/DRR programming and implementation, by supporting the CoES to effectively take over the leading role in applying the community-based DP/DRR model.Through its new Education Centre, the regional CoES will be mentored to: i) lead a capacity building process through which an increased number of communities in East Khatlon will acquire and consolidate the skills to effectively contribute to DP/DRR at individual, village and regional levels; and ii) to develop and share learning in order to systematise its own achievements, along two strategic lines: inclusiveness, and innovation, particularly through synergies with developmement actions for greater resilience. At national level, Oxfam will actively engage with CoES and DipECHO partners for improved DRR policy, harmonisation of DP models and upscaling strategies.See Annex &quot;Institutionalisation of community-oriented DP/DRR&quot;.</narrative>
  </description>
